1. Fetching user names
	Can be found in /etc/passwd
	Use commands 'getent passwd' or similar

	1.1. Parse results of usernames
		Find UID range
		Determine which users can be logged in

2. Authenticate
	Use PAM to allow logins
	Research required

3. Fetch user session list
	Should be placed in some configuration file
	eg. .config/bcdm/sessions/*rc

4. Start Display session
	Launch an X or Wayland session by executing a script supplied by the user
	
5. A daemon to monitor the session and relaunch the login screen should the session end
	Research required
	Ensure minimal use of system resources

